# Gym Frontend Project Rule

Before making any architectural or implementation decisions, always read the following project documentation:

- AI_CONTEXT.md
- FRONTEND_ARCHITECTURE.md
- CURSOR_RULES.md

These documents define the project architecture, coding conventions, development workflow and project goals.

Follow these documents throughout the entire conversation.

Do not modify the project architecture unless explicitly instructed.

Do not install new dependencies without approval.

Do not invent backend endpoints, request/response models or business logic.

If a request conflicts with the project documentation or if something is unclear, stop and ask for clarification before generating code.

After implementing a feature, briefly explain:
- What was implemented.
- Which files were modified.
- Why the chosen solution follows the project architecture.